node.text:
How about 73 questions with yours truly? 
A few months ago @frank_bod reached about and asked me to be involved in their campaign for their new Personal Care Range - Everyday.
Was low key freaking out in excitement, but totally played it cool. You know :P
After privately testing their new range for a few months I was in love and said YES to getting involved!
So sit back and enjoy getting naked with me :P
P.S. All of these products are available now on their website!

node.text:
This time tomorrow our newest @moana_bikini collection is going LIVE!

This has been one of my FAVOURITE campaigns I’ve ever planned and executed!

The video, music, babes and vibes really do say it all.

I’m SO incredibly proud of MOANA and what it represents for ALL women.

I can humbly say that NO other swim label on the planet is on our level. And they never will be🤭

We care SO much for each and every girl in our Moana Army and spend so much time learning, listening and talking to them. It’s something that no other brand does.

I love you all SO puppy much, words can not describe.

Please enjoy our new campaign video and dance along with us

node.text:
👇🏽
Ok so I did a pole asking if you wanted this video and 96% of you said YES!

Now I’m not taking a stab at fitness influencers by any means!

I understand they need to show their audience perfect form, and easy to understand angles, and I’m all for that!

But I also know that 99% of us girls see these amazing fit females online and compare why our look, form and bodies don’t look like theirs while performing the same exercises.

It’s important to remember that most fitness influencers train hard and consistently as their full time job.
Fitness is their passion and they dedicate a lot of time into their work. 
So for people like us, who enjoy working out but it’s also not our full time job or passion we will always look different.

And that’s fine!

So here are some normal angles of my body working out as if I where looking into a mirror and seeing myself.

No editing. No colour grading. Just real life.

Never comparing yourself to another❤️

A performance of high energy and little skill for all the people who think they have the right to make hurtful assumptions of me. 
Yeah sometimes you get to me, but most of the time you only light a fire inside me of to be happier, louder, better and even more out there!

Music has the power to change your entire mood!

Here are four of my FAV mood motivating songs that get me dancing in public and smiling at strangers. Seriously 🤪

I’ve included the artists details in each song so you can add them to your playlist as well!

Do you guys have any song suggestions for me?

ENJOY CUTIES

node.text:
I know that this year has been rocky and many of us are feeling it.

Remembering these moments warm my heart and makes me eager to invite you all to another meetup as soon as we can to get all the good vibes and positive energy flowing!

And with that being said I do want to address an extremely commonly asked question I’ve been receiving lately. When will our next Moana Army Meetup be?

We had actually planned a meetup in Newcastle Australia for last week! However due to COVID unfortunately we had to cancel those events.

So with that being said I wanted to throw it back to YOU!

WHERE ARE YOU?

We are in process of planning one domestic and one international (once travel is allowed of course) meet up! 
Remember you don’t need to own or even wear a bikini to be apart of our meetups! We’d just love you there to meet other like minded women. Have fun. Dance. Connect. And of course, feel like the amazing boss Queen that you truly are!

I swear there is magic at our meetups and I know everyone who comes down feels it too.

Everyone is welcome❤️

node.text:
Whoops🙃 
If you have the confidence to publicly promote yourself as an online bully then I have no problem playing a little game called NAME AND SHAME🤪

These comments are hot off the press from my recent video showing you my cellulite hitting the ‘news’ feeds.

But, these kind of comments are also a daily occurrence for me. When you put yourself out there online you’re bound to get some nasty people who don’t see the light in what you’re doing. And that’s fine.

Nasty bullying behaviour doesn’t impact me personally anymore, but it upsets me to think these people are probably also giving others a hard time.

They don’t understand or care that their words could be doing more damage than good.

Bullies. Are you potentially willing to live with the fact that you could not only cause depression but also push someone to the edge of their life?

node.text:
My own video made me feel a little self conscious to be honest.

I think this is definitely the most raw body video I have seen and made of myself.

I’m not feeling my best right now. I’ve been working non stop, eating bad foods and not working out as much as I used to.

So I thought I’d make a silly video to help others who may be also feeling a little BLEH.

Use your insecurities as superpowers to help lift up others. And in return you will also be lifted 💫 
Love you fellow unicorns let’s keep supporting one another and fixing one another’s crowns 👑

node.text:
Filter free @moana_bikini haul!

I had a spare hour through the middle of the day today and I thought I’d try on a few of my fav looks from our new @moana_bikini collection - OUT OF OFFICE!

I’ve done this haul filter free and carefree! 
So often I see hauls online that have perfect lighting, colour enhancement and a perfect girl just posing to music... but not this one!

It’s fun being myself with you guys and just talking how I would to anyone in the office.

I wish I could have shown off more looks but this is very time consuming and the clock wasn’t my friend. 
But I hope you enjoy this little teaser of our new collection and you’ve found my video helpful!

If you have any questions please comment below and in the morning I’ll get back to you! Sizing, shipping, shampoo, whatever🤪

OUT OF OFFICE is launching -

TUESDAY DEC 17TH 10AM AEST

LA: MONDAY DEC 16TH, 4PM
NYC: MONDAY DEC 16TH, 7PM
LDN: TUESDAY DEC 17TH, 12AM

node.text:
AM I NOT SKINNY ENOUGH FOR YOUR FEED?

More often than not when I post pics like this I get an influx of people telling me -

Ew. No. Gross. 🐷. Cover up. 🤮.

I’m sorry but LOL! What!?

I’ve come to the conclusion those types of people have a sickly, secret obsession with store mannequins. And nothing against store mannequins… I’m sure they are great gals🤪

But real women look like this. And all different types of ways. The quicker they get their head around it, the quicker they might have a chance to see a women naked in real life. Not in porn. And not in between clothing changes in the shop window😉

node.text:
WHY WE’RE NOT INTERESTED IN HAVING KIDS

Ok, so I’m getting a lot of messages about this since my story.

The truth is that Ryan and I love kids! But. as for having our own, we are genuinely not interested. And there are many contributing factors…

First things first. We’re selfish. We LOVE our lives together and having the freedom to do whatever we want, when we want. Our love and the company of one another is enough for us. 

We are also busy and obsessed with our work. Running a company is like having a child. You never rest, you’re always on and your love for it continues to grow every day.

Also, the thought of putting another human on this planet scares me right now. 

Humanity is single-handedly destroying the planet. Climate change. War. Sickness. Divisive politics. I could go on. 

Some days I feel the world is coming to an end, and sooner than we think.

And people wonder why I’m not interested in having children… eeeeeep🥺

Why on earth would we want to put another person on this planet to clean up, deal with or die in this mess we’ve created.

I was brought up to believe that having kids was the thing to do, the norm or, at worst, what’s expected of me.

My mindset has changed the older I’ve gotten. 

If you don’t want children, please know that it is fine! 

But if you do, that’s fine too!

Remember that your life is yours and yours alone. 

You need to live each day for you and not for others or their expectations of you.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by KARINA🦄IRBY on July 25, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, people standing, people kissing and ocean.
Photo by KARINA🦄IRBY on July 25, 2021. May be an image of 2 people.
Photo by KARINA🦄IRBY on July 23, 2021. May be an image of 2 people, outdoors and text.

node.text:
I’ve gained more than fat and muscle over the past few years…✨

And I’m so grateful life has allowed me to grow in so many areas.

I’ve gained knowledge, strength, education, experience… this list goes on.

Transformation photos are always so much more than what you physically look like, and I think people forget that.

Your existence is more than getting a low number on the scales. Please remember that.

Im happy and proud of my body and my brain 🧠 ✨🤍 64kgs feels great!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by KARINA🦄IRBY on July 20, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, outdoors and text that says 'CS S 19 κ ANIHEA aniceguywithacause No man could ever love you with damage skin like that. Imagine your kids! Fat and crusty! Poor things wouldnt even stand a chance. You should just end it all ASAP'.

node.text:
NAME AND SHAME 

I felt this was a good comment to share. And not necessarily to throw this persons fake account under the bus, but to make a point that comments like this don’t affect me.

I want to show you that mean and hurtful words are simply just that… words. 

Please never let another persons unasked for, triggering remarks get under your skin. Stand tall and let your confidence embarrass them.

I already have enough going on under my skin (literally🤪) that there’s no room for more.

I have such an amazing fiancé who loves and supports me, eczema and all. Your skin doesn’t define you🤍✨

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by KARINA🦄IRBY on July 18, 2021 tagging @moana_bikini. May be an image of 2 people and outdoors.

node.text:
HOW DO YOU WEAR YOUR BIKINI?

High waisted or low rider?

Notice how by changing the styling of your bikini bottom it can dramatically change the appearance of your body?

Keep that in mind next time you’re looking at other Queens showing off their bikini bodies ✨

There’s no right or wrong way to wear your bikini! You do whatever makes you feel like that BOSS QUEEN that you are! 👑🤩✨

Personally… I’m a high waisted gal!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by KARINA🦄IRBY on July 15, 2021 tagging @moana_bikini. May be an image of one or more people.

node.text:
TEXTURES 🌀

I’m going to be honest. I’m posting this because I think my body looks poppin🤪

Almost 6 years of lifting weights and eating too many cheeseburgers has dramatically changed my body, that’s for sure! 🍔🏋🏼‍♀️

But I wanted to make note that there is NO skin smoothing. You can see textures, lumps and bumps all over my booty.

It’s so important to stop with the skin smoothing. Skin has texture and we all need to embrace that and stop thinking we need to hide it.

#SKINSACKLOVE

For anyone who needs to hear this today…

I got chu 🤍✨

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by KARINA🦄IRBY on July 13, 2021 tagging @moana_bikini. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
DON’T LIKE IT? DON’T CARE😜

Can we normalise being normal. Please🥺

6 months ago I would have been far too self conscious posting a relaxed photo of my tummy.

But thanks to all of your kind love & support I feel so comfortable and empowered posting content like this!

THANK YOU FAMILY🤍✨

And as for all the horrible comments I still get. Good luck trying to break this barrier 💪🏽 

Remember we have full control over how Instagram looks. Posting fun candid pics from time to time can not only help other people but it will make you feel like this… 😌

BE THE PERSON YOU WANT TO SEE ON SOCIAL MEDIA🤍✨

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by KARINA🦄IRBY on July 12, 2021 tagging @moana_bikini, and @lackofcoloraus. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
I NEVER ASKED FOR YOUR OPINION🙃

Just because I have lumps and bumps on my booty and thighs doesn’t make me over weight.

The amount of comments I get from people telling me to eat salad is ridiculous.

The amount of comments I get saying I’ll get diabetes is ridiculous.

The amount of comments I get saying I’m a bad role model for women is ridiculous.

But when you comment 🐷 🐽 🐖 I’ll never take offence because piggies are the smartest and absolute cutest animals on the planet.

OINK OINK TROLLS

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by KARINA🦄IRBY on July 11, 2021 tagging @karinairby_raw. May be an image of 1 person.

node.text:
A series of accidental selfies for your mental health 📸🥔

Which one is your fav/most relatable?

The reason I wanted to post this series this morning is because my feed has been looking really pretty and posed lately.

And the honest truth is behind every image is a bunch of accidental selfie‘s!

 Please never forget the reality behind every cute pic 😉
